SU(2) BK plateau-escape certificate
Date: 2026-07-23

Source:
  ginibre_q3/character_ring_iter/search_su2_bk_local_escape.cpp

Strict build:
  g++ -O2 -std=c++20 \
    -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion -Wshadow -Werror \
    ginibre_q3/character_ring_iter/search_su2_bk_local_escape.cpp \
    -o /tmp/search_su2_bk_local_escape

The checker enumerates ordered valid queue paths directly.  For every target
position it assigns signs by degree, so equal irreducible labels cannot occur
in both sign supports.  It computes (delta,f) with the signed two-queue
transfer.  Every displayed witness was independently checked by direct
subset enumeration.

For every negative state it removes the target constraint and verifies
  target_free_total=2*total,
  target_free_delta=2*delta       (even minus parity),
  target_free_delta=0             (odd minus parity).

For every state requiring more than two moves, it independently computes
the global source totals O and P by the ordinary SU(2) Clebsch--Gordan
recursion.  A run fails only if an O>P state has a closed plateau or requires
more than N moves to reach a lower (q,o) value.

