Thus every delayed composite state in this complete source-deficit domain
has the minimal possible deficit delta=-2.  Lemma 22F3A16 proves that a
composite state with this deficit has exactly two excursions and
f=2 modulo 4.  The factor histogram further shows that every delayed state
has one rigid positive excursion factor.  The replay is evidence for the
patterns later formulated as Targets 22F3K2--22F3K3.  The exact
counterexample below refutes those targets outside this bounded domain.

