The final two jobs are the rigid excursion
  alpha=[3,0], beta=[0,3], signs=[-,-].
Removing them gives the primitive four-step state (P22.30N7).  The
appended pair preserves its long internal escape while changing the global
source dimensions to O>P.  This exact state refutes Targets
22F3K, 22F3K2(1), and 22F3K3(2).  It retains the square-free prefix and
zero-transfer scheduling normal forms in Targets 22F3J--22F3M.

