The normal search is constrained independently: proper-prefix generators
are square-free, every prefix transfer is zero, all strict scheduling
moves have one orientation, and at most two are strict.  The extremal
analyzer enumerates the complete zero-transfer plateau component, contracts
exact threshold ties, constructs the strict scheduling DAG, and checks all
reachable sinks and sources for a descending boundary.  These are exact
bounded checks of Targets 22F3R and 22F3R1, not proofs.

