Negative-excursion release audit:
  /tmp/search_su2_bk_local_escape source 9 2
  source_nonprimitive_negative_states=4238
  source_composite_no_normal_negative_excursion=0
  result=PASS

For each composite state, the checker splits at every internal return,
selects each negative signed excursion factor, and independently searches
its local plateau component.  A factor counts as released only when its
local word has length at most its job count, square-free proper prefix, and
at most one positive prefix transfer.  This is exact bounded evidence for
Target 22F3P.

